I was just using http://cupcakeipsum.com/ to insert some dummy text into the editor. Instead of the provided _COPY TO CLIPBOARD_ button I selected the text and copied it into the editor. I got the following error message on save {code}The editor content could not be parsed. There is a problem at line 1, column 552. Parser message: Undeclared namespace prefix "ng" (for attribute "bind") at [row,col {unknown-source}]: [1,552]{code} The paragraphs there contain custom attributes, e.g.
{code}
<span ng:bind="paragraph.text" class="ng-directive ng-binding">Powder marzipan gummi bears caramels halvah tootsie roll ice cream I love liquorice. Biscuit candy canes marshmallow. Tart jujubes tart powder fruitcake toffee candy. Cake biscuit caramels bear claw pie lollipop bonbon apple pie. Candy bear claw lollipop cake apple pie. Sesame snaps cake I love tiramisu candy canes I love bear claw I love. Bonbon sweet roll bonbon liquorice toffee ice cream I love powder pudding. Ice cream I love pastry sweet. I love tiramisu cheesecake halvah icing tiramisu. Jujubes chocolate soufflé marshmallow brownie pie sweet jelly. Cotton candy dessert cheesecake gummies soufflé chocolate cake halvah. Gummi bears chocolate lemon drops chocolate ice cream pastry. Pie marzipan brownie chocolate tootsie roll carrot cake.</span>
{code}
which is the [bind|http://docs.angularjs.org/guide/directive] directive of AngularJS.

The problem here is that we expect well-formed XHTML for the transformation into the storage format, and that _ng:bind_ is a namespaced attribute, but there is no schema registered for the ng namespace. Imo we should [disable this check on the parser|http://xerces.apache.org/xerces2-j/features.html] or purge the HTML so that this stuff gets removed as the actual error is confusing to the common user.

